.TH "dmam_alloc_attrs" 9 "dmam_alloc_attrs" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dmam_alloc_attrs \- Managed dma_alloc_attrs()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" dmam_alloc_attrs
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *dma_handle "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ","
.BI "unsigned long attrs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to allocate non_coherent memory for
.IP "size" 12
Size of allocation
.IP "dma_handle" 12
Out argument for allocated DMA handle
.IP "gfp" 12
Allocation flags
.IP "attrs" 12
Flags in the DMA_ATTR_* namespace.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed \fBdma_alloc_attrs\fP.  Memory allocated using this function will be
automatically released on driver detach.
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to allocated memory on success, NULL on failure.
